snippet.title: Syrup 2013 Film | Amber Heard, Shiloh Fernandez, Kirstie Alley
snippet.description:
What's your review of the 2013 film Syrup? It's directed by Aram Rappaport, and stars Amber Heard, Shiloh Fernandez, and Kirstie Alley. About Syrup 

Wondering where to watch Syrup ? If you know anywhere to stream or watch Syrup  full movie online free, feel free to share this information! Most of the films and TV shows I review can be found on Amazon Prime, Netflix, Disney Plus, DVD, or blu-ray.

Syrup  plot from IMDb: "A slacker hatches a million-dollar idea. But, in order to see it through, he has to learn to trust his attractive corporate counterpart. Based on Max Barry's novel."

The trailer can be found online.

Cast and Characters:
Amber Heard as Six, the Addy marketing executive.
Shiloh Fernandez as Scat, the protagonist.
Kellan Lutz as Sneaky Pete, Scat's former roommate and company rival.
Brittany Snow as Three, Pete's assistant.
Josh Pais as Davidson.
Kate Nash as Beth.
Rachel Dratch as Clerk
Adam LeFevre as Priest
Christopher Evan Welch as Davies
Zachary Booth as Chet

Directed by Aram Rappaport
Written by Aram Rappaport, Max Barry
Based on Syrup by Max Barry
Produced by Cameron Lamb, Barrie M. Osborne, Susan A. Stover
Cinematography: Julio Macat
Edited by Robert Hoffman
Music by Peter Bateman, Andrew Holtzman, Paul Saunderson
Production company: Lila 9th Productions
Distributed by Magnolia Pictures
Release date: June 7, 2013 (US)
Budget: $2.5 million (estimated)
Box office: $663
